WEBVTT

00:01.593 --> 00:05.267
[Both breathing heavily]

00:05.302 --> 00:07.674
You and Dave gonna fag
it up at Pottery Barn

00:07.709 --> 00:09.402
and get matching dishes and shit?

00:09.437 --> 00:10.309
This is how it's gonna work?

00:10.344 --> 00:12.398
Every time I meet a guy, you gonna
send someone to almost kill him?

00:12.433 --> 00:15.082
- [Crackling]
- [Water splashes]

00:20.283 --> 00:21.497
[Gasps]

00:21.532 --> 00:22.747
You really scared me, okay?

00:22.782 --> 00:24.135
You can't just sneak in like that.

00:24.170 --> 00:27.384
Patrick: That happens
again, look, you call me.

00:28.810 --> 00:31.379
Do you know what that is?
Is that Baz, Pope, Julia?

00:31.414 --> 00:34.196
What about Julia and
Baz? Were they close, too?

00:34.231 --> 00:36.015
I have an idea for a job.

00:36.017 --> 00:36.696
[Glass shatters]

00:36.731 --> 00:39.239
Paul: Please tell me they
did not take my briefcase.

00:39.274 --> 00:40.880
Some of those files are classified.

00:40.915 --> 00:42.722
How bad do you want those files back?

00:42.724 --> 00:44.056
♪♪

00:44.058 --> 00:45.480
J just broke up with me.

00:45.515 --> 00:47.098
- Why?
- Like I know?

00:47.133 --> 00:49.439
Take a shower, put on
your wire, go to school.

00:49.474 --> 00:51.097
He trusts me.

00:51.194 --> 00:52.798
Smurf: I think I knew this guy.

00:52.800 --> 00:55.301
Boy, I'd love to get back
in touch with him again.

00:55.303 --> 00:59.194
♪♪

00:59.229 --> 01:00.840
Hi there, kiddo.

01:00.842 --> 01:04.543
♪♪

01:04.545 --> 01:10.549
♪ She stares deeply ♪

01:10.551 --> 01:14.453
♪ Locked inside me ♪

01:14.455 --> 01:17.556
♪ Burnin' brightly ♪

01:20.315 --> 01:26.078
♪ One they know that I cannot take ♪

01:26.163 --> 01:29.535
♪ Waitin' for it all to begin ♪

01:29.537 --> 01:32.805
♪ Every night now, they'll win ♪

01:36.443 --> 01:39.278
♪ Come and meet my black hole ♪

01:39.280 --> 01:43.282
♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:43.284 --> 01:46.886
♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:46.888 --> 01:50.723
♪ I've got a big black hole ♪

01:50.725 --> 01:54.994
♪ I've got a big
black, big black hole ♪

01:54.996 --> 01:58.827
♪ Got a big black hole inside of me ♪

01:58.862 --> 02:01.132
♪ Got a ♪

02:02.262 --> 02:04.403
Is this really the best time?

02:04.405 --> 02:05.689
I mean, I can't find J anywhere.

02:05.724 --> 02:07.271
Pope's been in the yard since 6:00 a.m.,

02:07.306 --> 02:09.675
punching his stupid bag.

02:09.676 --> 02:11.934
[Chuckles] You... you can't get laid here?

02:11.969 --> 02:14.613
Did I forget to ask your permission?

02:14.615 --> 02:16.606
Hand these out to your brothers.

02:20.987 --> 02:24.223
[Scoffs] This is less than
the half that we normally get.

02:24.225 --> 02:27.071
You're a property manager.
That's your paycheck.

02:27.106 --> 02:28.531
[Chuckles] Wait.

02:28.566 --> 02:31.171
You expect us to live
on our actual salaries?

02:31.206 --> 02:32.982
You gotta give the boys a little somethin'.

02:33.017 --> 02:34.320
You know them. They need shit.

02:34.355 --> 02:35.701
They're ready to hit a mini-mart.

02:35.703 --> 02:37.670
- They are or <i>you,</i> Baz?
- [Zipper whirs]

02:37.672 --> 02:40.104
We're talking about having another kid.

02:40.170 --> 02:41.604
We're gonna need a bigger place.

02:41.639 --> 02:43.409
Another kid?

02:43.510 --> 02:44.522
What?

02:44.557 --> 02:49.348
I'm just wondering if it's the best
time for you to knock up Catherine now.

02:49.350 --> 02:52.184
Uh... I can handle it.

02:52.186 --> 02:53.853
I'm sure you can.

02:54.104 --> 02:56.574
It's all there. Just get it done.

03:04.965 --> 03:07.933
[Grunting]

03:10.866 --> 03:13.105
Deran: What's your problem, Pope?

03:13.107 --> 03:16.121
[Continues grunting]

03:16.156 --> 03:18.737
You know, Smurf's taking
off for the weekend.

03:18.772 --> 03:22.848
Toby's taking her to Vegas.
Some French circus shit.

03:22.986 --> 03:25.384
I think Toby's gonna be our new dad.

03:25.386 --> 03:29.345
Don't be jealous, baby.
It's not a good look.

03:29.380 --> 03:31.574
Now the kid from the
7-Eleven is gonna call

03:31.621 --> 03:33.893
when they start selling more phone cards.

03:33.928 --> 03:34.994
We need to be ready.

03:35.033 --> 03:36.423
Why don't we just tell Paul he's in?

03:36.458 --> 03:38.536
I mean, we have all this confidential shit.

03:38.571 --> 03:40.675
- What are we waiting for?
- If you come at him with threats,

03:40.710 --> 03:42.277
he's gonna stand up on principle.

03:42.312 --> 03:43.667
What are you, a psychologist now?

03:43.702 --> 03:45.871
You want someone next to you
who doesn't wanna be there?

03:45.873 --> 03:48.523
I don't want a guy next
to me that I can't trust!

03:48.558 --> 03:52.181
[Punching resumes]

03:52.216 --> 03:54.613
I'm easing him in. Just give me a few days.

03:54.911 --> 03:57.045
Anybody heard from J?

03:59.451 --> 04:02.821
Well, somebody better find out
what's going on with that kid.

04:03.210 --> 04:05.657
When this phone rings, answer it.

04:05.692 --> 04:09.395
Here's $1,000. Have fun. See you tomorrow.

04:09.544 --> 04:12.198
Deran: Hey, bring a
rubber. Toby gets around.

04:12.200 --> 04:14.533
[Punching continues]

04:16.194 --> 04:18.594
- [Sighs]
- Morning.

04:19.697 --> 04:21.130
Morning.

04:25.645 --> 04:27.212
[Plate clatters]

04:28.638 --> 04:29.748
[Sighs]

04:29.750 --> 04:32.704
[Dog barking in distance]

04:32.739 --> 04:35.663
So I'm a pretty terrible cook,

04:35.733 --> 04:38.207
but it's food.

04:38.566 --> 04:40.799
[Dish clatters, utensil clinks]

04:44.465 --> 04:47.466
You know, it's not... typical

04:47.951 --> 04:50.896
for teachers to have their
students spend the night.

04:51.601 --> 04:53.043
[Utensil clinks]

04:53.078 --> 04:56.308
I'm sorry. I should
get... I should get back.

04:56.503 --> 04:58.533
Wait, that's it?

04:58.568 --> 05:00.713
You just show up here, all freaked out,

05:00.748 --> 05:03.716
don't tell me anything,
and now you're leaving?

05:03.843 --> 05:05.852
I'm sorry. I don't think so.

05:06.076 --> 05:08.854
You're not going anywhere
until you talk to me.

05:09.191 --> 05:12.258
Come on. You know I can keep a secret.

05:18.141 --> 05:22.067
My uncle just got out of prison.

05:22.162 --> 05:24.629
- Which one?
- Pope.

05:26.809 --> 05:30.042
He, uh... [Clears throat] he robbed a bank.

05:30.044 --> 05:33.846
[Inhales deeply] He wasn't alone, but...

05:34.072 --> 05:36.102
he was the only one that got caught.

05:37.540 --> 05:39.523
Who else was with him?

05:42.512 --> 05:45.824
They were all in on it. All of them.

05:46.178 --> 05:47.783
My other uncles, my grandmother.

05:47.818 --> 05:51.764
You know, she's the one
that's kind of in charge, so...

05:51.766 --> 05:54.395
In charge? You mean, like...

05:54.430 --> 05:57.202
they've done this kind of thing before?

05:57.316 --> 05:59.638
And you found out.

05:59.752 --> 06:01.890
Is that why you're so scared?

06:03.130 --> 06:04.930
Then what is it?

06:09.478 --> 06:11.664
They're planning something else.

06:15.837 --> 06:18.157
[Panting]

06:18.815 --> 06:21.026
You training for something
we don't know about?

06:21.028 --> 06:24.897
[Continues panting]

06:24.899 --> 06:26.496
Pope, if I had known about the pills...

06:26.531 --> 06:27.937
You knew!

06:27.972 --> 06:30.736
No. I would've told you.

06:30.844 --> 06:34.907
There is no way that she drugged
me without you signing off on it.

06:34.983 --> 06:37.109
You knew.

06:37.204 --> 06:40.105
She wants you to find out
if I'm still taking 'em?

06:43.101 --> 06:45.984
I can't tell which version
of me you like better...

06:46.019 --> 06:47.032
drugged up or crazy.

06:47.067 --> 06:51.604
I kinda think you like me
crazy. Less competition.

06:53.727 --> 07:24.883
♪♪

07:24.918 --> 07:26.625
Whoo!

07:26.660 --> 07:36.769
♪♪

07:38.000 --> 07:44.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

07:53.319 --> 08:05.297
♪♪

08:05.299 --> 08:06.398
Uhh!

08:06.400 --> 08:10.502
♪♪

08:12.616 --> 08:15.205
You know, maybe we
should go back to Belize.

08:16.907 --> 08:20.846
You know, surf Long Caye,
swim with turtles and shit?

08:24.484 --> 08:28.147
You know, I was thinking maybe it could
just be you and me this time. [Sniffs]

08:29.523 --> 08:32.558
[Surf rolling]

08:32.559 --> 08:35.561
[Sea birds calling]

08:35.563 --> 08:36.828
What's wrong?

08:40.900 --> 08:43.202
What?

08:43.354 --> 08:44.543
I saw Dave yesterday.

08:44.578 --> 08:46.763
He's got some kind of
infection in his lungs.

08:46.798 --> 08:49.026
He's back in the hospital.

08:49.912 --> 08:51.910
You guys still...

08:52.182 --> 08:54.179
Nope. [Sighs]

08:54.181 --> 08:56.048
Maybe we could go to the D.R.?

08:56.584 --> 08:59.755
You know, go in December, surf Encuentro.

09:01.326 --> 09:03.336
- What's up, Adrian?
- Hey, Craig.

09:04.254 --> 09:05.424
How is it?

09:06.226 --> 09:09.747
It's pretty good. It was
really fat earlier. Yeah.

09:10.844 --> 09:12.598
- You been competing?
- [Liquid sloshes]

09:12.658 --> 09:14.040
Uh, here and there.

09:14.105 --> 09:17.162
Oh, must be why we haven't seen you.

09:18.471 --> 09:20.213
No, I've been around.

09:20.248 --> 09:21.729
Ran into Toby in the lot.

09:21.764 --> 09:23.772
Guess who doesn't know shit about Vegas?

09:23.807 --> 09:24.977
Seriously?

09:24.979 --> 09:27.192
Hasn't talked to Smurf in a week.

09:27.227 --> 09:29.313
She left us a grand. I mean, what
are we supposed to do with that

09:29.348 --> 09:31.845
except throw a balls-out party?

09:31.880 --> 09:34.781
You pencil us in or you
got an ESPN interview to do?

09:38.115 --> 09:39.806
Yeah, you should come.

09:40.825 --> 09:42.253
Guess I'll be there.

09:42.288 --> 09:43.600
All right.

09:50.717 --> 09:52.224
You did good.

09:52.259 --> 09:54.710
See? It's not that hard
when you put your mind to it.

09:54.745 --> 09:57.315
Good. Well, what? Can you arrest them now?

09:57.350 --> 09:59.781
I mean, he implicated the entire
family. It's all on the wire.

09:59.816 --> 10:02.417
He talked about a 3-year-old
crime he wasn't witness to.

10:02.452 --> 10:04.422
A few small-time B&Es.

10:05.978 --> 10:08.918
It's good. You got him talking.

10:08.953 --> 10:12.286
Now we get him talking specifics...
the next job, his role in it.

10:12.321 --> 10:14.351
<i>His</i> role?

10:14.353 --> 10:16.821
No, I thought you said
we had to get him out.

10:16.856 --> 10:18.719
If J cooperates, he can plead down.

10:18.754 --> 10:21.925
A felony conviction would ruin his life.

10:22.035 --> 10:24.161
He's a smart kid. He
should be going to college.

10:24.236 --> 10:26.146
I mean, Jesus, his mom just died.

10:26.181 --> 10:27.987
Plenty of ex-convicts have
made something of themselves.

10:28.026 --> 10:30.867
No, no, no. You told me
that I could help him.

10:30.948 --> 10:33.870
I am doing this to protect him.

10:34.055 --> 10:36.206
Let me be very clear.

10:36.302 --> 10:39.509
You are in this situation
because you are weak and selfish.

10:39.571 --> 10:43.213
And you're gonna get yourself out of
this situation by being weak and selfish.

10:43.256 --> 10:44.915
That's who you are.

10:45.031 --> 10:48.132
If you wanna tell yourself you
care about this kid, be my guest.

10:48.167 --> 10:50.418
But you will do whatever you
need to do to get him talking

10:50.453 --> 10:52.760
because you don't want to go to prison.

10:55.458 --> 10:57.575
I owe you big-time.

10:57.610 --> 10:59.688
- [Chuckles] No, I was happy to do it.
- No, I do. I do.

10:59.723 --> 11:01.719
I just feel bad my guy
couldn't get the computers.

11:01.765 --> 11:03.042
The asshole already sold 'em.

11:03.077 --> 11:05.435
Oh, forget that. Let me take you to dinner.

11:05.437 --> 11:07.338
Right? Or... or let me buy you a car.

11:07.373 --> 11:08.593
- [Laughing]
- If I could afford one,

11:08.628 --> 11:10.711
I-I would buy you a car today.

11:10.746 --> 11:12.810
No. Okay.

11:12.915 --> 11:15.579
You know what, though?
While I have you here...

11:15.798 --> 11:17.482
I got a problem with our books.

11:17.517 --> 11:18.369
You want me to look at something?

11:18.404 --> 11:21.799
No, no, no, just some advice. Um...

11:21.841 --> 11:23.757
We made a little more
money on our properties

11:23.792 --> 11:25.555
than we'd like the federal
government to know about.

11:25.590 --> 11:28.701
Mm. Little tax evasion, money laundering...

11:28.736 --> 11:30.029
- [Laughs] No.
- ...that sort of thing.

11:30.064 --> 11:31.326
Is that what we're discussing?

11:31.363 --> 11:33.627
No, no, no. Neither.

11:33.662 --> 11:35.629
Hypothetically...

11:35.712 --> 11:38.279
if someone wanted to move some money

11:38.395 --> 11:42.939
and save it for later, how would he do it?

11:42.941 --> 11:44.716
- Hypothetically?
- Yeah.

11:44.751 --> 11:46.967
[Paul and Baz speaking
indistinctly, dog barking]

11:47.002 --> 11:48.942
Paul: ...plumbing, electrical business.

11:48.977 --> 11:50.958
- Something to maintain your building.
- Baz: Hmm.

11:50.993 --> 11:53.178
And then you would pay that
vendor for services rendered,

11:53.213 --> 11:54.500
only you're the vendor.

11:54.535 --> 11:56.253
Well, the problem with
that is everybody's done it.

11:56.288 --> 11:58.161
The IRS is kind of hip to it,

11:58.196 --> 12:00.210
which is what made offshore
accounts so appealing

12:00.245 --> 12:03.246
back in the day, but now there's a...

12:03.431 --> 12:04.582
Actually, I gotta go.

12:04.617 --> 12:05.630
My car is in the shop,

12:05.665 --> 12:08.303
and I gotta get my kid
to baseball practice.

12:08.338 --> 12:10.100
Oh. Yeah. Take the Challenger.

12:10.102 --> 12:11.331
[Keys jangle]

12:11.366 --> 12:12.903
- Really?
- Yeah.

12:12.992 --> 12:14.981
I got plenty of cars around
here I can use. Take it.

12:15.016 --> 12:16.284
Saving my ass again?

12:16.319 --> 12:17.950
- Yes, I am.
- Thank you.

12:17.997 --> 12:19.791
I'll bring it back, uh,
this afternoon. Your place.

12:19.826 --> 12:20.684
Yeah.

12:20.746 --> 12:22.212
Thanks.

12:27.248 --> 12:28.655
How's Nicky?

12:30.468 --> 12:32.695
J.

12:32.747 --> 12:35.424
You guys are young. I understand that.

12:36.021 --> 12:38.499
But you were kinda harsh
on her, weren't you?

12:39.665 --> 12:40.767
Yeah. I'm sorry, I just...

12:40.802 --> 12:42.741
No, it's okay. You know,
it's none of my business.

12:42.776 --> 12:45.187
I just... [Inhales deeply]

12:45.222 --> 12:46.756
[Sighs deeply]

12:46.802 --> 12:48.468
Take care of yourself.

12:57.770 --> 13:00.301
Hey, look, I'm... I'm
sorry about last night.

13:01.376 --> 13:03.487
You know, I was walking
around the beach all night,

13:03.489 --> 13:06.623
thinking about what you said. And...

13:06.763 --> 13:09.226
I tried to call Nicky to get her back.

13:09.506 --> 13:11.294
You know, I didn't want to
come home until I fixed things,

13:11.329 --> 13:12.157
but I couldn't.

13:12.192 --> 13:15.165
If you care about her,
you're gonna stay out of this.

13:15.167 --> 13:17.567
You try to warn her, I promise you,

13:17.741 --> 13:19.694
she's gonna get hurt.

13:21.658 --> 13:23.607
- Go get some breakfast.
- [Bottle scrapes]

13:23.642 --> 13:26.676
[Footsteps depart]

13:38.289 --> 13:41.458
[Sea birds calling]

13:44.424 --> 13:46.943
Thought I'd never hear from you again.

13:46.978 --> 13:48.757
Did you get it done?

13:49.768 --> 13:53.537
Yeah, I screwed their
cameras up pretty good.

13:53.539 --> 13:57.823
Won't be able to get a technician
in to fix it till Monday.

13:57.858 --> 14:00.471
They're flyin' blind all weekend.

14:00.694 --> 14:02.412
[Sighs]

14:04.048 --> 14:06.158
You stealing cars now?

14:07.437 --> 14:10.538
This is business, baby. That's it.

14:14.156 --> 14:18.625
Just a guy you call when
you need something up north?

14:18.660 --> 14:20.727
No.

14:20.933 --> 14:24.801
You're an old friend
who's doing me a favor...

14:24.912 --> 14:27.012
because I paid you.

14:29.838 --> 14:31.489
Yeah, all right.

14:33.078 --> 14:34.455
How's Craig?

14:34.512 --> 14:35.977
Fine.

14:36.012 --> 14:37.971
That's all I get?

14:38.784 --> 14:41.251
Look, my boys don't know about this,

14:41.253 --> 14:43.233
and I don't want 'em to.

14:44.746 --> 14:46.417
He still look like me?

14:46.485 --> 14:48.487
He never did.

14:48.805 --> 14:50.368
[Scoffs]

14:51.964 --> 14:54.323
Good seeing you, too, Smurf.

14:55.867 --> 14:58.248
Take it easy. [Chuckles]

15:09.127 --> 15:12.263
You know, that shit's terrible for you.

15:12.351 --> 15:15.370
Humans aren't built to
digest cheese and shit.

15:15.441 --> 15:16.973
Lactose.

15:17.756 --> 15:19.596
Are you following me?

15:19.631 --> 15:21.665
You don't return my calls.

15:21.727 --> 15:24.407
Had to track you down.

15:24.442 --> 15:26.509
You're staying at a hotel now?

15:26.610 --> 15:29.038
Catherine finally realized
she could do better?

15:29.094 --> 15:30.814
Just a rough patch.

15:33.669 --> 15:35.086
Imagine my surprise when I heard

15:35.121 --> 15:37.780
someone cut a hole in the wall
of a strip mall in San Marcos

15:37.815 --> 15:40.176
and jacked a safe from
a landscaping business.

15:40.211 --> 15:41.486
I got your cut.

15:41.521 --> 15:42.867
We were supposed to do that job together.

15:42.902 --> 15:45.753
I never agreed to that.

15:47.719 --> 15:50.077
I'll find something for us to do together.

15:50.112 --> 15:53.020
I just haven't been able
to find the right thing.

15:53.055 --> 15:55.912
Well, you're in luck
'cause I'm full of ideas.

15:56.595 --> 15:57.637
Like what?

15:57.672 --> 15:59.338
[Chuckles]

15:59.644 --> 16:02.775
Last time I told you
about a job, you jacked it.

16:02.864 --> 16:05.865
No, this one's solid. I've
been casing it all week.

16:05.937 --> 16:09.619
You in? Or you need the
okay from the family?

16:10.275 --> 16:12.524
[Slurping]

16:12.559 --> 16:14.115
Yeah, I'm in.

16:15.247 --> 16:17.247
[Yak's "Use Somebody" playing]

16:17.249 --> 16:19.816
♪♪

16:19.818 --> 16:22.986
[Sea birds calling]

16:33.512 --> 16:34.939
Cath?

16:36.427 --> 16:37.394
- Hey.
- Hey.

16:37.429 --> 16:38.809
[Bag thuds]

16:38.844 --> 16:41.597
Got these weird crackers
Lena likes. Where is she?

16:41.632 --> 16:44.981
Playing four square down the street.

16:45.016 --> 16:46.978
Angela's watching her.

16:48.318 --> 16:49.971
[Chuckles]

16:50.006 --> 16:52.615
- Oh, shit, no.
- [Both laugh]

16:52.650 --> 16:54.484
No, I can't. I can't. I
got too much shit to do.

16:54.486 --> 16:55.079
Five minutes.

16:55.114 --> 16:56.653
- No, no, no.
- Six.

16:56.655 --> 16:58.046
- Cath...
- Maybe 15.

16:58.081 --> 16:59.678
[Chuckles] Please.

16:59.713 --> 17:01.458
No, I can't.

17:01.460 --> 17:03.026
You forget how to make a baby?

17:03.028 --> 17:04.661
[Laughs] After the job, okay?

17:04.663 --> 17:06.548
We're not gonna have
sex till after the job?

17:06.583 --> 17:08.330
Look, look, look, look. Listen to me.

17:08.333 --> 17:11.134
When the money's clean
and we got a new house...

17:11.273 --> 17:15.438
[Whispers] I'll get you
so pregnant. I promise.

17:15.473 --> 17:17.473
What'd she say?

17:17.509 --> 17:19.608
Who?

17:19.611 --> 17:21.731
You know who.

17:21.766 --> 17:24.492
She doesn't want you to
have another baby with me?

17:25.022 --> 17:26.204
Two days ago, you were begging me.

17:26.240 --> 17:28.339
Smurf didn't say anything. Come on.

17:30.985 --> 17:32.976
Vin: I'll take the
teller. You take the guard.

17:33.011 --> 17:35.158
There's only one. He's about
to collect social security.

17:35.160 --> 17:37.459
Pope: It's the middle of the day.

17:37.494 --> 17:39.268
That's the point.

17:39.359 --> 17:41.187
They close down for lunch.

17:41.250 --> 17:43.900
We go in as soon as they re-open.
It'll just be the two employees.

17:43.902 --> 17:45.713
Have you ever hit a bank?

17:45.748 --> 17:48.295
You can't just go in with guns.

17:48.373 --> 17:50.691
- How many cameras?
- Four.

17:50.806 --> 17:54.388
One on the door, one behind the
teller, and two in the main room.

17:54.430 --> 17:57.028
We're gonna wear ski masks.

17:57.065 --> 17:58.448
When we get in...

17:58.483 --> 17:59.538
[Metal ball rattles]

17:59.573 --> 18:01.860
- ...black out the rest.
- Except we're already on camera.

18:01.895 --> 18:05.987
There's one... two right
here in the parking lot.

18:07.292 --> 18:10.953
First thing the cops will
do is pull the tapes. No.

18:12.524 --> 18:15.011
I'll find us a job. This isn't it.

18:15.046 --> 18:16.546
Yeah?

18:16.665 --> 18:18.732
See, it's hard to believe a guy

18:18.804 --> 18:21.271
when he's lied about everything else.

18:21.273 --> 18:25.175
Catherine's not your wife, for example.

18:25.270 --> 18:28.278
You thought I wouldn't find out?

18:28.495 --> 18:30.043
Maybe you just thought I'd never get out,

18:30.078 --> 18:32.662
so you promised me shit
you couldn't deliver.

18:34.520 --> 18:35.501
What do you think your brother will say

18:35.536 --> 18:38.723
about you jacking off to his
girl the past three years?

18:38.758 --> 18:40.524
[Inhales sharply]

18:42.228 --> 18:45.230
You do what you want.

18:45.397 --> 18:49.423
I ain't going back to
prison for you or anybody.

18:58.524 --> 19:00.025
[Inhales sharply]

19:00.145 --> 19:02.268
♪♪

19:02.303 --> 19:04.081
[Sniffs]

19:06.780 --> 19:08.881
[Engine revs]

19:11.725 --> 19:14.328
[Engine turns off, car door opens]

19:14.443 --> 19:15.876
[Car door closes]

19:16.934 --> 19:19.001
- Hey.
- [Hose thuds]

19:19.271 --> 19:21.003
Don't you know we're in
the middle of a drought?

19:21.038 --> 19:22.488
Yeah, don't tell the DWP.

19:22.523 --> 19:23.606
- [Laughs]
- How was the game?

19:23.641 --> 19:26.309
Terrible. The kids can't
hit. They can't catch.

19:26.344 --> 19:28.177
It was like watching paint dry.

19:28.179 --> 19:30.442
Yeah, you should see Lena dance.

19:30.477 --> 19:31.507
Anyway, thank you.

19:31.542 --> 19:32.459
- Oh.
- All right?

19:32.494 --> 19:33.153
- Yeah.
- I gotta go.

19:33.188 --> 19:34.540
- Okay.
- Lydia's picking me up at the pier.

19:34.575 --> 19:35.687
- Sure, man.
- I appreciate it.

19:35.722 --> 19:39.648
- Hey. Take this.
- What's that?

19:39.683 --> 19:41.324
Uh, I talked to my finance guy.

19:41.359 --> 19:43.274
Turns out the tip you
gave is gonna pay off.

19:43.309 --> 19:45.282
It's a little... little thank you note.

19:45.331 --> 19:46.927
We were talking hypotheticals.

19:47.031 --> 19:48.937
Hypothetically, there's 5 grand in there.

19:48.972 --> 19:52.112
IRS doesn't come sniffin'
around for 5 grand, right?

19:52.870 --> 19:55.517
- I-I can't take this.
- You already did.

19:56.944 --> 19:58.577
Baz.

20:02.000 --> 20:05.002
♪♪

20:07.967 --> 20:09.501
[Shifts gears]

20:12.389 --> 20:14.738
♪♪

20:14.773 --> 20:18.375
[Tool whirring in distance]

20:32.933 --> 20:36.045
Man: You must be Rachel.

20:36.047 --> 20:38.462
Isaiah. How was your flight?

20:38.497 --> 20:40.817
It was perfect. I slept all the way.

20:40.852 --> 20:42.590
Well, it's good to meet you finally.

20:42.625 --> 20:43.531
And you.

20:43.566 --> 20:45.739
And there she is. She's a beauty.

20:45.817 --> 20:48.461
- Oh, yeah.
- You're still serious about your purchase?

20:48.516 --> 20:49.355
You bet I am.

20:49.390 --> 20:51.977
I wouldn't have flown in
from Austin if I wasn't.

20:52.012 --> 20:53.213
[Chuckles]

20:53.248 --> 20:54.949
Well, why don't we go
start on the paperwork?

20:54.984 --> 20:56.651
Sure. Sure.

21:00.804 --> 21:03.906
[Dog barking in distance]

21:07.002 --> 21:09.703
[Door creaking]

21:12.778 --> 21:14.216
Alexa?

21:23.522 --> 21:24.922
Alexa?

21:26.730 --> 21:28.230
[Soft moan]

21:28.232 --> 21:29.432
[Door creaks]

21:29.434 --> 21:31.140
Oh. Oh.

21:31.175 --> 21:32.519
- [Groans, sniffles]
- You okay?

21:32.554 --> 21:34.693
No, I just thought...

21:34.728 --> 21:36.383
I dropped... something.

21:36.465 --> 21:38.058
I'm fine, Josh.

21:38.093 --> 21:39.075
[Vomits, coughs]

21:39.110 --> 21:41.340
Oh, God. Okay. Okay. Okay, come on.

21:41.375 --> 21:42.870
- [Cries, groans]
- Come on, let's go to the bathroom.

21:42.905 --> 21:45.063
- Come on.
- [Groans]

21:45.098 --> 21:46.192
- I'm sorry.
- Come on.

21:46.227 --> 21:47.608
- [Sniffles]
- Now, now, come on. You're okay.

21:47.643 --> 21:49.919
- [Whispers] I'm sorry.
- You're okay. No, it's fine.

21:49.921 --> 21:53.852
- [Sniffles]
- Come on.

21:53.887 --> 21:54.876
- [Vomits]
- Ugh.

21:54.911 --> 21:55.620
[Coughing]

21:55.655 --> 21:58.180
Oh. Okay.

21:58.215 --> 21:59.288
[Groans]

21:59.323 --> 22:02.101
Okay. Uh, how much did you take, Alexa?

22:02.167 --> 22:05.275
[Voice breaks] Just a little.
I swear it was just a little.

22:05.310 --> 22:06.671
Okay.

22:06.706 --> 22:08.821
Okay, we're gonna have
to get you to a hospital.

22:08.902 --> 22:10.701
No, no, no, no. No.

22:10.815 --> 22:14.589
No, they'll take... my job.

22:14.673 --> 22:17.847
- Okay.
- They'll take... my whole...

22:17.922 --> 22:21.467
No, no. Come on, wake up.
Keep... No, no, stay awake.

22:21.502 --> 22:22.648
No, stay with me.

22:22.683 --> 22:24.353
Alexa, Alexa, stay with...

22:24.355 --> 22:25.261
- [Vomits]
- Okay.

22:25.296 --> 22:28.124
- [Coughs]
- [Sighs]

22:28.126 --> 22:28.873
[Shower running]

22:28.908 --> 22:31.078
I'm fine. [Groans]

22:31.113 --> 22:33.213
[Whispers] Careful.

22:40.042 --> 22:42.203
[Grunts]

22:42.238 --> 22:45.504
You okay? [Panting]

22:45.559 --> 22:47.269
- I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

22:47.304 --> 22:48.924
I'm so sorry.

22:48.959 --> 22:50.292
It's all right.

22:53.878 --> 22:55.791
These your kids?

22:55.849 --> 22:56.907
Grandchildren.

22:56.942 --> 22:58.308
Oh.

22:58.388 --> 22:59.662
They live nearby?

22:59.697 --> 23:01.557
Mm, East Coast.

23:01.632 --> 23:02.989
When my wife and I got divorced,

23:03.024 --> 23:05.907
she convinced Caitlyn
to move to Connecticut.

23:05.942 --> 23:08.245
- Mm.
- I get 'em at Christmas.

23:08.280 --> 23:09.534
Mm.

23:10.568 --> 23:14.288
So... how did you become a collector?

23:15.893 --> 23:19.910
My mother loved cars. I
think I got it from her.

23:20.960 --> 23:23.445
Paperwork's almost done.

23:23.480 --> 23:25.425
Now there's no rush.

23:25.460 --> 23:29.334
You take her for a long,
long spin and sleep on it.

23:29.408 --> 23:32.231
And I will. I can't wait.

23:38.027 --> 23:41.660
That's a great picture of you. Who took it?

23:41.695 --> 23:43.564
That's not me.

23:46.441 --> 23:48.142
Looks like you.

23:49.341 --> 23:51.173
[Plastic crinkles]

23:51.269 --> 23:53.269
- [Cabinet door closes]
- [Exhales]

23:59.997 --> 24:01.457
It's okay.

24:06.254 --> 24:07.768
[Whispers] Thank you.

24:09.304 --> 24:10.648
[Whispers] Okay.

24:10.844 --> 24:12.377
Thank you.

24:22.138 --> 24:23.272
Mm.

24:38.783 --> 24:41.290
Daddy told me he'd take you swimming.

24:41.325 --> 24:44.693
[Indistinct conversations]

24:44.695 --> 24:45.599
<i>♪♪</i>

24:45.634 --> 24:47.244
[Water splashes, girl screams]

24:47.318 --> 24:48.718
Lena!

24:50.921 --> 24:52.395
[Grunts]

24:52.430 --> 24:54.061
Got you a present.

24:54.108 --> 24:56.699
Baz did not tell me that you
guys were having a keg party.

24:56.734 --> 24:59.235
'Cause I didn't invite him.

24:59.458 --> 25:02.359
Wanna get in some trouble?

25:02.394 --> 25:04.782
- Let's go.
- All right, but be careful.

25:05.650 --> 25:08.217
<i>♪♪</i>

25:08.219 --> 25:11.520
[Indistinct conversations, laughter]

25:15.014 --> 25:17.132
Do you ever see any sharks?

25:17.962 --> 25:19.367
Yeah, sometimes.

25:19.444 --> 25:21.911
Wow. How big?

25:22.010 --> 25:23.824
Well, they're usually baby great whites,

25:23.859 --> 25:27.093
so they can be, like, 6 feet, 5 feet.

25:28.200 --> 25:29.681
[Sniffs]

25:29.716 --> 25:31.816
Will you excuse me?

25:31.909 --> 25:37.479
[Whooping and laughter]

25:37.481 --> 25:39.756
♪♪

25:39.791 --> 25:41.032
Come on.

25:51.854 --> 25:54.187
What's up? Huh?

25:54.241 --> 25:55.620
What?

25:55.871 --> 25:57.499
Huh? What?

25:57.603 --> 25:59.935
I'm just talking to her. What's going on?

26:00.070 --> 26:02.638
I don't care who you talk to.

26:02.640 --> 26:05.464
Okay, then. Then stop acting like
someone died and have some fun.

26:05.499 --> 26:07.832
It's a party. That's
what you do at a party.

26:08.045 --> 26:09.554
Is that an order?

26:11.048 --> 26:12.818
What is your problem?

26:14.643 --> 26:18.487
I don't want your brother throwing me
off a boat in the middle of the night.

26:18.568 --> 26:21.016
You said to be here, so I'm here.

26:21.792 --> 26:23.525
Okay, you know what?

26:23.527 --> 26:25.900
You wanna go? Then go. I don't give a shit.

26:27.349 --> 26:28.648
Okay.

26:28.799 --> 26:30.699
[Footsteps depart]

26:30.701 --> 26:33.535
<i>♪♪</i>

26:37.213 --> 26:39.392
[Groans]

26:39.461 --> 26:41.962
Remember when he wasn't
an asshole? [Scoffs]

26:42.113 --> 26:44.327
♪♪

26:44.447 --> 26:45.641
[Spits]

26:46.796 --> 26:48.150
Okay. Ready?

26:48.252 --> 26:51.220
[Water running]

26:53.264 --> 26:54.528
[Faucet turns off]

27:00.435 --> 27:02.045
How are you feeling?

27:08.036 --> 27:09.529
[Whispers] Thank you.

27:14.637 --> 27:16.105
[Glass clatters]

27:16.709 --> 27:18.125
I, um...

27:20.654 --> 27:22.991
I was in a car accident

27:24.014 --> 27:27.121
a few years ago, and, um...

27:28.604 --> 27:30.659
I started taking Oxy.

27:30.709 --> 27:33.050
And somewhere along the way...

27:33.164 --> 27:35.216
Yeah, my mom did heroin.

27:36.848 --> 27:38.491
That's how she died.

27:43.940 --> 27:45.763
[Whispering] I was sober.

27:47.635 --> 27:50.569
I had six months.

27:50.642 --> 27:51.752
I'm trying.

27:51.787 --> 27:53.886
- Yeah.
- I'm trying.

27:55.013 --> 27:59.839
[Crying] I just been under
a-a lot of... pressure.

28:00.865 --> 28:03.459
[Exhales deeply]

28:08.855 --> 28:10.359
J...

28:21.270 --> 28:22.731
J.

28:25.638 --> 28:28.575
Please, please, please.

28:29.086 --> 28:33.093
Let me. Let me do this.

28:33.257 --> 28:36.258
♪♪

28:38.495 --> 28:41.497
[Clinking]

28:58.147 --> 29:00.482
[Moaning]

29:09.254 --> 29:12.811
[Surf rolling]

29:12.846 --> 29:14.454
You Baz?

29:16.569 --> 29:18.257
Yeah. Who are you?

29:18.295 --> 29:21.125
I'm Vin. A friend of Pope's.

29:21.426 --> 29:22.685
Okay.

29:22.797 --> 29:24.680
He never told you about me?

29:24.754 --> 29:26.354
No.

29:26.389 --> 29:29.323
Doesn't surprise me.

29:29.457 --> 29:32.515
We shared a cell at Folsom.

29:32.592 --> 29:35.860
Wasn't always easy. I'm
sure you can imagine.

29:35.918 --> 29:39.538
Guard shot him up with so much
Thorazine, he was droolin',

29:39.588 --> 29:43.089
makin' up lies to get himself through it.

29:43.271 --> 29:46.801
Was tellin' people your girl was his,

29:46.836 --> 29:49.719
your kid was his.

29:49.754 --> 29:51.887
What do you want?

29:52.170 --> 29:53.574
Well, your brother made me some promises.

29:53.609 --> 29:54.874
Then go talk to him.

29:54.909 --> 29:59.218
Oh, come on. I know
you're the guy in charge.

29:59.220 --> 30:01.704
I'm a hard worker, got
my own set of skills.

30:01.739 --> 30:05.207
I'm value add, man. [Laughs]

30:06.194 --> 30:10.163
[Sea birds calling]

30:10.165 --> 30:13.699
Pope would've died in
there if it wasn't for me.

30:13.701 --> 30:17.284
Now I'm coming to you out of respect.

30:18.873 --> 30:20.640
But I could go to Catherine...

30:20.642 --> 30:22.484
You stay away from her.

30:28.248 --> 30:31.009
You just figure it out with your brother.

30:31.086 --> 30:32.921
All I know is...

30:34.271 --> 30:35.947
you're cuttin' me in.

30:37.742 --> 30:39.242
That...

30:43.964 --> 30:48.097
♪♪

30:48.132 --> 30:49.498
Aah!

30:49.637 --> 30:53.072
[Indistinct conversations, laughter]

30:53.074 --> 30:56.509
<i>♪♪</i>

30:56.511 --> 31:00.424
[Diving board rattles, water splashes]

31:00.459 --> 31:03.316
Oh!

31:03.318 --> 31:05.478
Hey, baby, go say goodbye to Uncle Craig.

31:05.513 --> 31:08.319
I stopped by the bar. You weren't there.

31:08.354 --> 31:09.299
You gotta stop doing that.

31:09.334 --> 31:12.792
Just let me get it out.
Let me get this out.

31:12.794 --> 31:15.039
<i>♪♪</i>

31:15.074 --> 31:16.536
- I gotta go.
- I hate that.

31:16.571 --> 31:19.072
I hate the way you look at me. I hate it.

31:21.489 --> 31:24.172
It's... it's like you're scared of me.

31:25.140 --> 31:27.974
<i>♪♪</i>

31:31.234 --> 31:34.036
I'm taking these pills now,

31:34.100 --> 31:37.198
and I'm doing it for you. Okay?

31:37.233 --> 31:38.532
Pope, you...

31:38.567 --> 31:41.568
It... it just feels like...

31:41.603 --> 31:46.130
you're the only person who
wasn't afraid to be alone with me.

31:48.596 --> 31:51.664
<i>♪♪</i>

31:55.903 --> 31:59.172
[Whooping and laughter, water splashing]

31:59.174 --> 32:01.941
<i>♪♪</i>

32:08.415 --> 32:12.227
[Indistinct conversations]

32:12.262 --> 32:14.571
Yo, Jen's throwing up in the bushes.

32:14.606 --> 32:16.873
Oh, shit. Really?

32:16.915 --> 32:18.881
All over my mom's succulents.

32:18.916 --> 32:19.886
- [Sighs deeply]
- [Speaks indistinctly]

32:19.921 --> 32:22.195
Yeah, uh, she's asking for you.

32:22.197 --> 32:24.071
[Groans]

32:24.106 --> 32:25.633
Give me a second.

32:30.737 --> 32:32.954
- 10 minutes.
- Oh, give me a break.

32:32.989 --> 32:33.877
- That's all I needed.
- Yo.

32:33.912 --> 32:35.464
[Snaps fingers] Out.

32:35.499 --> 32:36.957
[Clears throat]

32:36.992 --> 32:38.572
Come on, babe, let's go.

32:39.940 --> 32:43.167
- What's up?
- Where's Adrian? [Sighs]

32:43.202 --> 32:44.881
I don't know. He took off. Who cares?

32:44.916 --> 32:46.487
I don't know give a shit
who you have sex with, man.

32:46.561 --> 32:48.359
Why do you think I invited him?

32:48.394 --> 32:52.091
I-I don't wanna talk about this
either, but just don't be an asshole.

32:52.093 --> 32:54.727
Adrian's a good guy. And this shit...

32:54.729 --> 32:56.762
is embarrassing.

32:56.764 --> 32:59.842
<i>♪♪</i>

32:59.877 --> 33:01.676
Does everybody know?

33:02.294 --> 33:04.284
[Pats leg] No, man.

33:04.772 --> 33:07.845
<i>♪♪</i>

33:07.880 --> 33:09.180
[Pats leg]

33:15.616 --> 33:18.818
♪♪

33:29.329 --> 33:31.393
[Cellphone alert chimes]

33:41.370 --> 33:44.042
_

33:58.755 --> 34:00.829
[Click]

34:08.068 --> 34:11.119
Wait. How'd a Texas girl grow up surfing?

34:11.188 --> 34:13.906
I lived all over the place.

34:14.018 --> 34:15.623
My mother loved to move around.

34:15.658 --> 34:18.099
She liked to see different things.

34:19.931 --> 34:23.380
Are you gonna tell me about that
picture of you in your office?

34:23.416 --> 34:26.050
You gonna tell me the truth?

34:26.085 --> 34:27.442
Yeah, you caught me.

34:27.476 --> 34:31.312
Yeah, so why did you lie
about such a silly thing?

34:31.391 --> 34:33.993
Feels like that was a whole lifetime ago.

34:33.995 --> 34:37.487
I did a lot of things back
then that I'm not proud of.

34:37.523 --> 34:41.625
So what, the picture's a reminder?

34:41.667 --> 34:43.000
Somethin' like that.

34:43.034 --> 34:46.237
Well, now now you got me really
interested. What did you do?

34:46.239 --> 34:50.559
[Laughs] Just the usual stuff.

34:50.594 --> 34:53.978
Broke a few hearts, crashed a few cars.

34:55.483 --> 34:57.617
That's it?

34:57.652 --> 35:00.032
What, not a good enough story for you?

35:00.067 --> 35:00.810
[Chuckles]

35:00.845 --> 35:03.236
You want me to make something up?

35:04.192 --> 35:07.193
♪♪

35:13.867 --> 35:16.408
Won't you excuse me for a moment?

35:17.338 --> 35:20.272
♪♪

35:27.047 --> 35:29.815
♪♪

35:32.419 --> 35:35.621
♪♪

35:37.524 --> 35:40.726
♪♪

35:46.190 --> 35:48.391
[Click]

35:48.536 --> 35:51.737
♪♪

36:02.901 --> 36:07.283
[Indistinct shouting and cheering]

36:13.240 --> 36:15.258
[Grunts]

36:15.260 --> 36:18.294
[Cheers and whistles]

36:31.944 --> 36:33.453
Your friend Vin just came to my house.

36:33.488 --> 36:35.144
How does he know where I live?

36:35.179 --> 36:36.546
He's been following me.

36:36.600 --> 36:39.734
Okay. He told me you made him
some promises. Is this true?

36:39.769 --> 36:42.704
What else did <i>Vin</i> tell you?

36:42.821 --> 36:47.490
<i>♪♪</i>

36:47.621 --> 36:51.794
I know you've always loved her,
ever since we were kids, okay?

36:51.796 --> 36:53.974
I know that. Cath is with me.

36:54.009 --> 36:55.081
I'm sorry. That's how it is.

36:55.116 --> 36:57.881
Yeah, Baz always gets what he wants.

36:57.961 --> 37:00.997
Of course she loves you. Of course
<i>I</i> scare the shit out of her.

37:01.040 --> 37:02.963
Baz wants something, he gets it.

37:02.998 --> 37:05.300
Doesn't matter what happens to anyone else.

37:05.335 --> 37:07.054
- Catherine.
- Oh, bullshit.

37:07.089 --> 37:09.422
- Julia.
- Smurf kicked her out, that's my fault?

37:09.474 --> 37:11.827
- If you hadn't...
- If I hadn't what?

37:12.417 --> 37:14.183
You think I killed her, don't you?

37:14.185 --> 37:15.883
That's what you think.

37:17.411 --> 37:19.589
Who told Smurf about Julia and me?

37:19.624 --> 37:23.484
Oh, Smurf just happened
to walk in on us? Bullshit.

37:23.519 --> 37:25.795
You played it wrong.

37:25.797 --> 37:28.631
<i>♪♪</i>

37:28.633 --> 37:30.133
[Inhales deeply]

37:30.135 --> 37:33.302
<i>♪♪</i>

37:33.304 --> 37:35.304
[Exhales]

37:44.381 --> 37:47.894
You're not the only
one that lost her, okay?

37:47.929 --> 37:50.257
I loved her.

37:50.349 --> 37:51.216
I loved your sister.

37:51.251 --> 37:54.480
She was supposed to be your sister, too.

38:07.465 --> 38:09.255
You should've told me how
bad it was for you in prison.

38:09.290 --> 38:11.023
Maybe I could've done something.

38:16.040 --> 38:18.745
Shall I get the keys?
We'll take it for a spin?

38:18.780 --> 38:21.026
Wait, talk to me about this one.

38:21.061 --> 38:23.079
- [Chuckles] This car?
- Yeah.

38:23.114 --> 38:24.987
1963 Chevelle.

38:24.989 --> 38:27.023
This is my first car.

38:27.025 --> 38:31.307
Total clunker, honestly,
but I'll never sell it.

38:31.342 --> 38:34.155
So this is the car that
started it all, huh?

38:34.190 --> 38:35.630
Mm-hmm.

38:35.665 --> 38:38.668
Saved all your money...

38:38.670 --> 38:39.874
[Car door creaks]

38:39.909 --> 38:42.710
Did odd jobs, stuff like that?

38:42.745 --> 38:44.696
It that how it worked?

38:44.793 --> 38:48.194
Actually, I sort of inherited it.

38:49.713 --> 38:51.237
Oh?

38:51.272 --> 38:54.814
Yeah, there was a woman. This was her car.

38:54.849 --> 38:56.315
Girlfriend?

38:56.386 --> 38:59.535
Yeah. Beautiful, wild.

38:59.601 --> 39:02.958
She lived in this car
for years, with a kid.

39:02.993 --> 39:04.222
Your kid?

39:04.257 --> 39:06.023
No, just hers.

39:06.058 --> 39:11.862
We were doing a lot of coke,
weed, following bands around.

39:12.082 --> 39:16.320
She got me into some small-time
robberies to pay for the drugs.

39:17.069 --> 39:19.569
How old was the kid?

39:19.696 --> 39:24.070
Must've been... [Sighs] 12, 13 maybe.

39:24.105 --> 39:28.172
You know, honestly,
Miriam was out of her mind.

39:28.207 --> 39:32.776
But the real reason I
stayed was for that kid.

39:32.852 --> 39:37.917
She was funny and smart and sweet.

39:38.327 --> 39:40.930
Sort of took care of us both.

39:40.932 --> 39:42.665
She loved to swim.

39:42.667 --> 39:46.402
[Chuckles] She'd stay in the
water till she turned blue.

39:46.404 --> 39:48.561
I called her "Smurf."

39:50.855 --> 39:53.175
I loved that kid.

39:54.512 --> 39:59.649
♪♪

39:59.651 --> 40:02.218
Hey, I got a bottle of
champagne in my office.

40:02.220 --> 40:05.755
Let me grab it, and we
can toast to your new car.

40:05.757 --> 40:08.925
[Footsteps depart]

40:22.914 --> 40:24.373
[Car door creaks, closes]

40:24.375 --> 40:27.343
[Dog barking in distance]

40:30.328 --> 40:31.885
- Hey.
- Hey.

40:31.920 --> 40:34.273
Making a smoothie. Do you want one?

40:34.308 --> 40:36.041
Sure.

40:36.249 --> 40:39.417
[Whirring loudly]

40:43.604 --> 40:45.701
_

40:47.892 --> 40:49.305
What's this?

40:59.676 --> 41:02.778
[Whirring stops]

41:02.780 --> 41:06.564
So you said they're
planning something else.

41:06.599 --> 41:08.827
Think they'll ask you to be a part of it?

41:12.484 --> 41:15.420
[Mouths words]

41:15.455 --> 41:17.421
[Crickets chirping]

41:21.465 --> 41:22.873
- [Cellphone ringing and vibrating]
- Woman: Wait, whose phone is that?

41:22.908 --> 41:26.135
- [Grunting] Huh?
- Whose phone is that? [Moaning]

41:26.137 --> 41:29.705
- [Ringing and vibrating continues]
- Oh, shit! Shit!

41:29.766 --> 41:31.159
What?

41:31.194 --> 41:33.378
- Where is it?
- [Ringing and vibrating continues]

41:33.413 --> 41:37.246
Aah! Goddamn it! [Sighs]

41:37.281 --> 41:39.360
[Ringing and vibrating continues]

41:39.395 --> 41:41.936
- [Cellphone beeps]
- [Panting] Hello?

41:41.971 --> 41:45.691
[Continues panting] When?

41:45.726 --> 41:47.446
Okay, thanks.

41:47.850 --> 41:49.949
- [Cellphone beeps]
- I gotta go.

41:49.984 --> 41:53.151
- Are you serious?
- [Belt buckle clinking]

41:53.186 --> 41:54.553
[Grunts]

41:56.195 --> 41:57.628
Hey.

42:00.023 --> 42:01.231
[Kisses]

42:01.877 --> 42:04.075
Sorry I missed you at Smurf's.

42:07.678 --> 42:09.798
- [Bottles clink]
- You still mad at me?

42:09.833 --> 42:11.033
No.

42:11.600 --> 42:13.666
- [Cap fizzes]
- No?

42:16.051 --> 42:18.314
What? What is it?

42:21.648 --> 42:23.083
It's Pope.

42:24.295 --> 42:26.469
He keeps coming around.

42:26.504 --> 42:27.977
He loves you.

42:29.444 --> 42:31.158
He always has.

42:32.546 --> 42:34.643
You can't blame him. Pope's Pope.

42:35.714 --> 42:38.710
Cath, everything's fine.
It's better than fine.

42:38.745 --> 42:41.746
We're about to pull a good
job here, life-changing money.

42:41.829 --> 42:42.428
But I...

42:42.463 --> 42:44.863
[Whispers] Cath, everything's good.

42:46.125 --> 42:48.515
[Knock on glass, door slides open]

42:48.550 --> 42:49.716
What is it?

42:49.751 --> 42:52.618
The guy called. I didn't
wanna call your cell.

43:00.430 --> 43:02.798
[Footsteps depart]

43:02.800 --> 43:03.502
What'd he say?

43:03.537 --> 43:05.248
The 7-Eleven on the base sold three times

43:05.283 --> 43:08.071
the number of phone cards
in the last two days.

43:08.106 --> 43:10.270
That only happens before they deploy.

43:11.803 --> 43:13.472
It's gonna happen this week.

43:20.751 --> 43:22.551
[Keys jangle]

43:29.025 --> 43:32.173
[Both breathing heavily]

43:32.208 --> 43:34.512
What? What?

43:34.547 --> 43:37.461
[Grunts]

43:37.496 --> 43:39.173
[Whispering] I just wanna be okay.

43:39.208 --> 43:41.042
I just want us to be okay.

43:41.077 --> 43:43.279
I just want it to be okay, please.

43:43.326 --> 43:45.025
Please?

43:48.730 --> 43:50.497
You wanna come inside?

43:51.944 --> 43:53.368
Come on in.

43:55.062 --> 43:57.262
You want me to come to a party?

43:57.358 --> 43:58.696
I'll be there.

43:58.731 --> 44:00.736
- Or we can go surfing...
- [Sniffs]

44:00.771 --> 44:02.837
Go to Belize.

44:02.967 --> 44:06.451
Whatever you want, man. You're
in charge. You made that clear.

44:07.331 --> 44:09.126
- [Dog barking in distance]
- But sorry,

44:09.161 --> 44:11.760
you can't make me feel something I don't.

44:14.572 --> 44:17.640
[Inhales and exhales deeply]

44:20.849 --> 44:21.982
[Sniffles]

44:25.475 --> 44:28.674
[Inhales deeply]

44:28.709 --> 44:31.076
[Footsteps depart]

44:32.688 --> 44:34.823
[Keys jangle]

44:37.791 --> 44:40.860
[Water running]

44:45.172 --> 44:46.543
[Dish clatters]

44:46.578 --> 44:48.911
[Turns off faucet]

45:00.970 --> 45:02.442
_

45:03.854 --> 45:06.288
[Closes drawer]

45:07.210 --> 45:10.764
[Dialing cellphone]

45:16.644 --> 45:19.145
[Line rings]

45:19.180 --> 45:20.509
Hey.

45:22.502 --> 45:25.430
Can you be my friend
right now and not a cop?

45:29.145 --> 45:30.846
[Sighs deeply]

45:33.835 --> 45:35.026
Hey.

45:36.568 --> 45:38.501
Help me, would you?

45:42.786 --> 45:45.546
I'm sorry about the whole Nicky thing.

45:46.347 --> 45:48.731
I hope you didn't take it personally.

45:50.453 --> 45:53.420
Baz says we need Paul, so...

45:53.531 --> 45:55.691
I guess we need Paul.

45:59.381 --> 46:02.633
[Clatter, bags rustling]

46:02.668 --> 46:05.379
He's mad you broke up with her.

46:05.883 --> 46:08.259
Says we can't trust you.

46:09.474 --> 46:13.149
I tried to tell him,
love makes you do shit.

46:14.292 --> 46:17.293
♪♪

46:23.767 --> 46:26.058
Goddamn animals.

46:27.414 --> 46:30.085
[Men shouting indistinctly, ball bouncing]

46:30.120 --> 46:32.074
Man: I got it, I got it!

46:32.076 --> 46:35.905
[Indistinct shouting continues]

46:35.940 --> 46:37.411
Paul: One sec, man. One sec.

46:37.446 --> 46:39.281
Man: Come on, bro! You gotta stay on it.

46:39.316 --> 46:40.611
Hey.

46:42.019 --> 46:43.694
Your wife told me where you were.

46:43.729 --> 46:45.765
Everything's cool, right? The car's cool?

46:45.801 --> 46:47.269
- Car is fine.
- All right.

46:47.304 --> 46:49.571
I thought I was gonna have
a little more time with this.

46:49.760 --> 46:52.094
With what?

46:52.096 --> 46:55.463
[Sighs deeply] I'm just
gonna take a gamble,

46:55.498 --> 46:57.640
and I'm gonna tell you the truth, okay?

46:58.991 --> 47:01.958
Should I sit down for this? [Laughs]

47:02.039 --> 47:04.215
How do you think I got your briefcase back?

47:04.250 --> 47:06.708
Oh, Baz, I don't know, man. I don't...

47:06.743 --> 47:10.366
I know you don't wanna know.
Thing is, it was easy...

47:10.401 --> 47:13.053
'cause my brothers robbed your place.

47:13.544 --> 47:17.279
Awesome. Maybe you can
get my TV back. [Laughs]

47:17.555 --> 47:19.591
Doesn't that make the most sense?

47:19.688 --> 47:22.288
I mean, it makes a lot more sense than
I know a guy who knows the ins and outs

47:22.323 --> 47:23.956
of the criminal underworld.

47:24.095 --> 47:27.554
[Siren wailing in distance,
ball continues bouncing]

47:27.589 --> 47:28.482
Why would you do that?

47:28.517 --> 47:31.076
'Cause you weren't ready
and you needed a push.

47:31.885 --> 47:33.100
Paul, you're a smart guy.

47:33.135 --> 47:35.838
You can spot an opportunity
when it presents itself.

47:35.840 --> 47:38.107
I'm about to present
you with an opportunity.

47:38.109 --> 47:40.275
♪♪

47:40.277 --> 47:41.644
You're blackmailing me?

47:41.679 --> 47:45.014
No. I know you'd stand
up to that sort of thing.

47:47.703 --> 47:48.648
You should get out of here.

47:48.683 --> 47:50.219
No, no, no, don't do that. Don't get angry.

47:50.254 --> 47:52.850
- I'm talking about a partnership.
- No.

47:52.885 --> 47:54.276
No, I'm not doing anything illegal.

47:54.349 --> 47:57.424
Well, you took my 5 grand,
you gave me those great tips...

47:59.414 --> 48:01.492
If you're gonna cross a line,

48:01.527 --> 48:03.870
you make sure it's a line worth crossing.

48:05.121 --> 48:07.888
Now you made 5 grand today.

48:08.085 --> 48:10.297
How'd you like to make some real money?

48:12.409 --> 48:17.646
[Birds chirping]

48:44.406 --> 48:46.140
How was Vegas?

48:50.210 --> 48:52.073
Craig ran into Toby.

48:53.950 --> 48:55.568
Where'd you really go?

48:55.603 --> 48:57.770
I'm tired, Baz.

49:02.031 --> 49:04.517
I talked to Paul. We're good.

49:06.419 --> 49:08.277
Good.

49:08.312 --> 49:09.878
You okay?

49:14.311 --> 49:15.748
Hey.

49:24.973 --> 49:26.541
Smurf...

49:29.832 --> 49:31.726
What happened?

